					<div id="post_message_420">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							prices for ibogaine vary, with a few places that supply rootbark, 5x extract, and whole root. It depends greatly what form you take the plant in of course. with root bark being roughly ten times as potent as the whole root. therefore if interested in a 5xextract one should inquire if this is extracted rootbark or whole root. NONE of these companys sell or ship to the united states. but some may sell to citizens from the US if using an address from outside the US. I was even given a positive word on iboga from a company that sells only to doctors or people who &quot;know the right people&quot;. this company though boasts they are the only ones selling internationally. their prices dont seem to add up when other companys are selling root for less. these types of claims can be common with some businesses dealing with herbs especially. I imagine there is large amounts of ibogaine being grown in more than a handful of countries worldwide. I imagine in 10 years the price could even go down. several other species of plants may provide extraction material more abundant than the iboga shrub ....maybe. Considering the price of the root, the treatment program I mention above probably isnt making a bunch of money on the ibogaine. A person could buy a half pound for around 500$ of rootbark. and probably have to do some sort of extraction on the product to consume. so 750$ for the ibogaine experience is pretty cheap considering that youre going to spend at least 3-4 hundred dollars on the ibogaine anyway. the other bonus would be that you either get a room at this persons house with the cost, or they take you camping up in the mountains. just having a guide for the day in mexico could easily run you 50-100$. So these people seem committed to providing a low cost experience, without advertising this or pushing in any way.
						</blockquote>
